ChatGPT said:

Awesome — I put a working single-file React app on the canvas that:

    Lets you enter all the fields (patient name/ID/facility, diagnosis, procedure, alternatives, “other risks,” signer/witness/MD/interpreter details).

    Renders a true 4-page, print-ready version of your UPMC consent with the exact language you pasted.

    Repeats the header (Patient Name / Identification Number / Facility / Page X of 4) and footer (*3CNTT* 3CNTT 02/16/2024) on every page.

    Has a Print / Save PDF button that hides the editor and prints on US Letter with proper margins and page breaks.

    Uses Tailwind + shadcn/ui for a clean, clinic-friendly UI and saves entries to localStorage so you don’t lose work on refresh.

If you want tweaks (logo placement, barcode, different footer date code, extra checkboxes like “transfusion refused,” or e-signature lines), tell me and I’ll wire them in.
